snippet.textDisplay: Natural is always best but I think that insight comes with age. I’m 29 now and so much more confident and comfortable with how I look now. I have my own hair, my own teeth, my own boobs, my own nails, my own eyelashes, no fake tan, no lip fillers and I’m content with that. Make up should be used to highlight our own natural beauty, not used as a mask to cover up what we have. I promise you’ll start to feel comfortable in your own skin if you let it breathe for a while, enjoy and embrace what you have and what you are and you’ll feel better for it.

snippet.textDisplay: I love how she doesn’t write ‘MY FILLER EXPERIENCE’ in the caption so you know she’s being absolutely genuine talking about her experience, unlike many YouTubers who would use it as click bait.
